A \, \sin (x + c) = \left(A \, \cos(c) \right) \, \sin(x)  + \left( A \, \sin(c)\right) \, \cos(x)
\sin (x) + \sqrt{3} \, \cos (x)
A \, \cos(c) = 1
A \, \sin(c) = \sqrt{3}
\sin^2 (x) + \cos^2 (x) = 1
A^2 = 4
A = 2
2 \cos (c) = 1
c = \pi / 3
\sin (x) + \sqrt{3} \, \cos (x) = 2 \sin (x + \pi / 3)
\sin
A \sin(x+c) = A \sin x \cos c + A \cos x \sin c
A,c
A \sin x \cos c + A \cos x \sin c = \sin x + \sqrt{3} \cos x
A \cos c = 1
A \sin c = \sqrt{3}
\tan c = \frac{A \sin c}{A \cos c} = \sqrt{3}
\tan c = \sqrt{3}
\sin c = \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}
\cos c = \frac{1}{2}
A \frac{1}{2} = 1
A = 2
\sin \frac{\pi}{3} = \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}, \cos \frac{\pi}{3} = \frac{1}{2}
\sin x + \sqrt{3} \cos x = 2 \sin ( x + \frac{\pi}{3})
A \sin x \cos c + A \cos x \sin c = \sin x - \cos x
A \cos c = 1
A \sin c = -1
\tan c = \frac{A \sin c}{A \cos c} = -1
\sin c = -\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}
\cos c = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}
A \cos c = A \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} = 1
A = \sqrt{2}
\sin (-\frac{\pi}{4}) = -\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}, \cos \frac{\pi}{4} = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}
\sin x - \cos x = \sqrt{2} \sin ( x - \frac{\pi}{4})
 a\sin(x)+b\cos(x)=\sqrt{a^2+b^2}\sin(x+y),\quad \tan(y)=\frac{b}{a},y\in(-\frac{\pi}{2},\frac{\pi}{2}) 
